{"title_page": "2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore", "text_new": "{{short description|Details of ongoing viral pandemic in Singapore}}\n{{Current disaster|event=disease pandemic|date=January 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=February 2020}}\n{{EngvarB|date=February 2020}}\n{{Infobox pandemic\n| name            = 2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore\n<!--Difficult to update, so no longer appropriate\n| map2            = COVID-19 Cases in Singapore by Planning Areas.svg\n| legend2         = {{center|Map of planning areas with confirmed (red) coronavirus cases (as of 11 March)}}\n-->\n| map3            = \n| legend3         = \n| disease         = [[COVID-19]]\n| virus_strain    = [[SARS-CoV-2]]\n| location        = [[Singapore]]\n| first_case      = \n| arrival_date    = 23 January 2020<br />({{Age in years, months, weeks and days|month1=01|day1=23|year1=2020|month2=|day2=|year2=}})\n| origin          = [[Wuhan]], [[Hubei]], China\n| recovery_cases  = 245<ref name=\"worldometers\">[https://www.worldometers.info/coronavirus/ worldometers.info]</ref><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| deaths          = 4<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\">[https://coronaboard.com COVID-19 Dashboard]</ref><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| confirmed_cases = 1,000<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"DashBoard\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\">[https://www.coronatracker.com/country/sg Corona Tracker Overview]</ref>\n| active          = 697<ref name=\"worldometers\"/><ref name=\"CTSG\"/>\n| suspected_cases = \n| total_ili       = \n| website         = {{url|https://www.moh.gov.sg/covid-19}}\n| First Case detected: = \n}}\nThe '''2020 coronavirus pandemic in Singapore''' is part of the [[2020 coronavirus pandemic|ongoing global pandemic]] of [[coronavirus disease 2019]] (COVID-19), a novel infectious disease caused by [[severe acute respiratory syndrome coronavirus 2]] (SARS-CoV-2). The first case of COVID-19 was confirmed on 23 January 2020.<ref name=\"Abdullah 2020\" /> To combat COVID-19, a Multi-Ministerial Committee was formed on 22 January with Minister for National Development [[Lawrence Wong]] and Minister for Health [[Gan Kim Yong]] as the Co-Chairs, along with other ministers and [[Deputy Prime Minister of Singapore|Prime Minister]] and Minister for Finance Mr [[Heng Swee Keat]] as an Advisor.<ref name=\"ST22Jan\"/><ref>https://www.moh.gov.sg/docs/librariesprovider5/default-document-library/multi-ministry-taskforce-on-wuhan-coronavirus-and-tor---final.pdf</ref>\n\n[[Singapore]] contributed US$500,000 to support [[WHO]] efforts against COVID-19.<ref>{{cite news |title=Singapore contributes US$500,000 to support WHO efforts against COVID-19 |url=https://www.channelnewsasia.com/news/singapore/singapore-contributes-s-500-000-to-support-who-covid-19-efforts-12568566 |accessdate=25 March 2020 |work=CNA |language=en}}</ref> In order to provide support to those in front lines, Singaporeans around the nation gave a round of applause. Health Minister Gan Kim Yong thanked the support given but reiterated the point that the greater support be practicing social distancing and reducing the work load on the healthcare workers.<ref>{{cite news |title=Singapore gives those on coronavirus front lines a round of applause |url=https://www.straitstimes.com/singapore/singapore-gives-coronavirus-frontliners-a-round-of-applause?login=true&close=true |work=The Straits Times |date=30 March 2020 |language=en}}</ref>\n\n{{2019\u201320 coronavirus pandemic data/Singapore medical cases chart}}\n== Statistics ==\nThe top plot shows the total number of cases as a function of time (by date) since 23 January 2020, the date of the first reported case in Singapore. The bottom plot shows the number of new cases as reported each day.\n{{Graph:Chart\n|type=line\n|linewidth=1\n|showSymbols=1\n|colors=orange, blue, red\n| legend=Legend\n| width = 900\n| height = 350\n| xAxisTitle = Date (day/month)\n| yAxisTitle = Total no. of cases (cumulative)\n| y1Title=Confirmed\n| y2T